yScreenFromWeb?topicID=8677.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plane Of Fear HELP</span><hr size=1> Fear can be done with two grps?  what lvl do those grps have to be?  And star what is meant by the aggro footprint?  I had fun but the two hours or so of total corpse recovery and bickering drove me nuts.<br><br>Hey Star - DONT YOU WORK?  I know your at work right now!<br><br>LMao, been on 4 raids, vox (2), naggy (1), and Fear (1)<br><br>And so far I hate raids.  Not enough goes on, especially naggy and vox = screw buff lines! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usagemonprayeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sagemon Prayeth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 331<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/13/02 2:13:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8677.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plane Of Fear HELP</span><hr size=1> We use a strategy similar to what Starborn described.  The north camp lemming run strategy sucks.<br><br>The hard part about breaking into Fear is the roamers around the portal.  There are a bunch of them -- gorillas, spiders, imps, amy warriors, the new BL armor mobs, and occasionally a fetid fiend or a tentacle terror.  Until the roamers are clear, the portal is a very dangerous spot.<br><br>What makes it especially tough is chain aggro.  If you aggro one mob, you may get 10.  Furthermore, chain aggro can cause a mob halfway across the zone to aggro your camp.  I've seen Terror death touch someone in the west camp.  Sometimes people will whine that the zone is bugged when that happens, but they're wrong.  That's just the way it works in Fear.<br><br>So what you can do is head to the west camp, do your best to control the inevitable swarm of mobs, kill as many as you can, then evac.  You reassemble at the portal, and do it again.  Once the roamers are dead, the plane is wide open.<br><br>If you're lucky, or very strong, you might not have to evac.  We've had two raids with a one-shot break at the west camp -- one was a pickup raid and the other was a guild raid.<br><br>Once you'd used the west camp strategy, you'll never make another north camp lemming run. <p>Sagemon Prayeth<BR>High Priest of Quellious the Tranquil<BR>A Twist of Fate</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utopdawgg19.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Topdawgg19</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/13/02 2:23:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8677.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plane Of Fear HELP</span><hr size=1> How is that aggroing one mob may get you ten?  I was also told last night that by hailing CT you have a 10percent chance of being HT?  Was that just BS&gt;?  <br><br>If that chain aggro is correct, then when you aggro one mob how come you dont get every mob of that same type? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uhawaiihouse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>hawaiihouse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 434<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/13/02 2:56:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8677.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plane Of Fear HELP</span><hr size=1> /sarcasm on<br><br>Wow Fear is cake!!<br><br>Cool so when you geting me and every other shaman in Ema