e time now, pretty much all of us are 60th level, and our equipment is pretty good.  The AE break is a HELL of a lot of fun, and is very fast, but has the potential to go to hell in a handbasket very, very quickly.<br><br>  Before Kunark, we'd zone in invis, head to the SW corner and kill anything that pathed our way first.  Then, once we'd cleared those mobs we'd procede to cautiously pull the zone using monks.  Occasionally we'd use monks to pull stuff away from the portal in before getting the guild to enter, but more often than not the monks would act as scouts, and give an indication when the portal was realitively free of mobs.  That might be the best option for you, it's slow and cautious but it does mean you won't get swamped too often.<br><br>Laoke <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uaaediasautumnwood.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aaedias Autumnwood</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/13/02 3:31:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8677.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~clanautumnwood/tanikaze/aaed.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PoF break?</span><hr size=1> our normal break in is 2-3 groups one solid group with highest war, highest enchie highest cleirc ranger(i get to pull) rogue and another baby healer(dru/sham) rest form up into decently blanced groups.. Buff to the max on all...all zone in turn to left about 80 degrees run to the wall AVOIDING the zombie house and commence to kill till you dead or they stop coming. If you die(normally die your very first time trying this) enuf is dead so can go in with backup gear while others loot and all 18 or so of the walkers is dead and you can start pulling the clumps. Something to have t