ngs get nasty ONE person will call for the evac.  SRO is good for this.  Then buff up, and get back to the portal ASAP.<br><br>5.  Send in the scout team.<br><br>6.  Have the first 3 groups assemble in line before the portal, ranked behind each other.  This helps keep the discipline, and sets the tone for the raid.  Tell them to start buffing.  Set your MA and 2nd MA keys.<br><br>7.  Tell your scouts to prepare for the break in.<br><br>8.  Once the scouts have judged the best time to enter, tell your troops to cast invis.  In 30 seconds tell G1 to enter.  Evey 6 seconds - order in another group.  Between calling the individual groups to charge, order the next groups up to the portal.<br><br>9.  Enter the portal, turn left, run to the wall.  Assist the main tank, fight until you die, evac, or win.  Once the camp is cleared, then med.  If you are a chanter or cleric, and get LOM, shout for Necro assistance.<br><br>This ends the break in Strategy.  Following are a few tips about fear (and raiding) in general.<br><br>1.  Always assist the MA.<br>2.  Only attack once the MA has build up aggro sufficiently.<br>3.  Never be sitting down when INC is called.<br>4.  If your pet screws up - get rid of it.  <br>5.  Expect to die.<br>6.  Expect to lose all random rolls.<br>7.  Dont spam any public channels.<br>8.  Have fun and dont be scared.  Your raid leader will look after you.<br><br>Meli<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usagemonprayeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sagemon Prayeth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 332<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/13/02 10:03:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8677.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Plane Of Fear break in guide</span><hr 